author: COMSOL
description: NO reduction occurs as flue gases pass through the channels of a monolithic reactor in the exhaust system of a car. Exothermic reactions in the reactor give rise to temperature gradients, and this example investigates the deformation of the reactor that occurs due to thermal stresses.
